threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, EABI4 version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, with debug_info, not stripped

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: ET CINS Active Threat Intelligence Poor Reputation IP group 262

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ELF binary is a DDoS (Distributed Denial of Service) bot, likely a variant of the Mirai or Gafgyt/Bashlite families, identified by its command-and-control logic and branding string 'DreamSec'. Upon execution, it forks into the background, connects to a hardcoded C2 server, and awaits commands to launch various network flooding attacks. The binary includes specialized functions for TCP, UDP, VSE (Valve Source Engine), and HTTP flooding, along with common botnet behaviors like system reconnaissance and process management.
